        "## Part 4\n",
        "\n",
        "The figure below follows the **Lecture 03 plotting style** and shows the gradient-boosted tree error rates by race, with the **Caucasian baseline** marked by a dashed line in each panel. The chart makes the same point as Part 3: African-American defendants have the highest FPR in the large groups, while Hispanic defendants show the highest non-zero FNR.\n",
        "\n",
        "I filtered to groups with at least **50 observations** so the figure stays publication-quality and is not dominated by extremely small categories such as Native American and Asian in this test split.\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ym8ef7gjOo57"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Publication-quality figure adapted from Lecture 03\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "\n",
        "er_plot = gbt_error_rates[gbt_error_rates[\"n\"] >= 50].sort_values(\"FPR\", ascending=False)\n",
        "navy, red = \"#00205B\", \"#B8192C\"\n",
        "colors = [red if race == \"African-American\" else navy for race in er_plot[\"race\"]]\n",
        "\n",
        "for ax, metric, title in [\n",
        "    (axes[0], \"FPR\", \"False Positive Rate by Race\"),\n",
        "    (axes[1], \"FNR\", \"False Negative Rate by Race\"),\n",
        "]:\n",
        "    ax.barh(er_plot[\"race\"], er_plot[metric], color=colors)\n",
        "    baseline = er_plot.loc[er_plot[\"race\"] == \"Caucasian\", metric].values[0]\n",
        "    ax.axvline(\n",
        "        baseline,\n",
        "        color=\"black\",\n",
        "        linestyle=\"--\",\n",
        "        linewidth=1.5,\n",
        "        label=\"Caucasian baseline\",\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    ax.set_xlabel(metric)\n",
        "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
        "    ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig(\"error_rate_disparity_assignment3.png\", dpi=150, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
